key_insights: Buy the rumor, sell the news pattern playing out across big tech earnings
Market not making new all-time highs despite big tech earnings not disappointing
Top 10 names controlling 40% of overall market, breadth starting to get exhausted
Trading volume typically declines significantly in November-December unless major catalyst
Fund managers up for the year likely won't risk performance before year-end
Gap fills only charted on daily timeframe, not lower timeframes
When halfway through a gap, typically pushes to bottom to close it completely
Chart on extended hours timeframe, then verify on regular hours for volume support
Don't fight strength - when everything green and one stock red, low probability it continues
Warren Buffett indicator shows market more overvalued than .com bubble and pre-COVID
AI spend concerns weighing on stocks - market questioning if ROI will justify expenditure
Look for fair amount of black space (no buyers) when playing puts
Use supply and demand analysis with regular vs extended trading hours
Golden zone (Fibonacci) for entry on pullbacks to strong levels

summary: Bill Fanter provides weekly market watchlist for November 3rd, analyzing post-big tech earnings action where SPY/QQQ failed to make new highs despite solid earnings. He emphasizes buy-the-rumor-sell-the-news pattern, discusses gap fill strategies on daily timeframes, and provides specific supply/demand zones for major names. Key theme is market overvaluation concerns and AI spending skepticism weighing on tech despite strong earnings, with reduced volume expected into year-end.
